{
  "texts": [
    "Certificates can aid developers in accurately identifying the actual presence and root cause of a bug.",
    "Such certificates could be a hint, like a bug anti-pattern, or a specific test case that triggers a program error.",
    "This section discusses the three mainstream approaches to bug finding.",
    "(1) Static analysis.",
    "Bugs reside within source code, and bugs can be identified by \"reading\" the source code and its associated artifacts, without the need to execute the program in a real environment."
  ]
}